-- Oriental Weavers to Invest $33 Million for Expansion, Borsa Says
-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 2012-06-13T09:40:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-13/oriental-weavers-to-invest-33-million-for-expansion-borsa-says.html
Oriental Weavers Co. (ORWE) , Egypt’s
biggest carpets manufacturer, plans to invest 200 million
Egyptian pounds ($33 million) on expansion projects this year,
 Al Borsa  reported.  The projects include starting the second phase of a
production facility in the fourth quarter and increasing by 60
percent the company’s machine-made carpet capacity when
completed, the Cairo-based daily said, citing investor relations
manager Haitham Abdel-Moneim.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  